< Review>
I recently ran over a nail in almost brand new large truck tires, luckily it was not through the sidewall. I decided to call Valley Tire & Tackle in Fort Jones to see if they had time and the ability to repair my tire. They said it would be super quick and that yes they could fix it for around $10+ dollars.

So I went in around 45 minutes later. They quickly took the truck back into the shop and went about removing the tire and getting to work. After about 15 minutes they were done. They brought my truck back out front and told me no charge - on the house this time. So I gave the worker who helped a few dollars as a tip.

Overall, my first experience with them was fantastic. Customer service was outstanding, price (if I paid) was more than reasonable, and its local which I love to support where possible. I recommend giving these guys a call first before heading up to Medford or Yreka - give them a chance to earn your business. I will be returning.</Review>

<Pics>None</Pics>< review>
I live in the Bay Area and I travel to Sacramento to see Dr. Smith. I have been her patient for over 11 years and no matter where I live in California, I make the trip to see Dr. Smith. Family n friends all think I'm crazy and try to recommend other dentists but none of them live up to Dr. Smith.

I have a severe phobia of dentists, struggle with anxiety and have a panic attack disorder. Dr. Smith's sedation services make dentistry possible for me despite my limitations. Other sedation dentists want to use IV sedation but Dr. Smith only uses the most minimally evasive options in all her work, including sedation. I know I'm a difficult patient but Dr. Smith makes me feel like her favorite patient and I am so grateful to have a dentist like her.

I tell her all the time, "If it wasn't for you, I would have no teeth." She smiles n laughs but it's true! No matter what it is that's keeping you from the dentist...fear, embarrassment, anxiety, or any other medical condition...you don't need to live in pain. Dr. Smith can and will fix it because everyone deserves to smile<//review>

< Review>
First and last time at this salon. They're not friendly at all. Not one nail was the same size as the rest. My index finger was crooked.. there was a bunch acrylic power underneath another nail. He never had me wash my hand so dust was trapped under the gel polish and I told him but he didn't listen and put my hand under the light anyway. I showed him the shape I wanted on their chart and he just went ahead and did square. When I asked him if he was going to do the shape I asked for, he raised his voice and said yeah but still didn't do it. I ended up just paying for horrible service and nails and had to pay to get them redone somewhere else.
Also paid for my daughter to get her nails painted with gel so it would last a little longer.. but the other guy didn't paint them completely and you could still see her nail through the polish on a few fingers.< /Review>

Marty Metro< /name>
< text>
OK, I have only written a few reviews in my life... but this one should be written!  My wife and I lived in San Fran years ago, so we know the area pretty well.  We went up for the weekend and decided it would be "fun" to rent a scooter for at least a few hours.  We TRIED to sign up for the "Scoot" application and found out AFTER signing up, that you can't put two people on oen scooter!  So, we walked over to Mr. Scooter!

WHAT A GREAT GUY!  We talked with the owner about how we wanted to put TWO people on a scooter and we wanted to be able to drive over the Golden Gate bridge. He helped us pick a GREAT scooter (I personally didn't think it would be big enough for me and my wife... but HE WAS RIGHT / I WAS WRONG) and gave us a GREAT price (he gave us a discount for multiple days).

In short, we got a GREAT scooter, NICE HELMETS and a lock to safely lock it up at night.  The owner (I think his name is Pedro, but I like calling him "Mr. Scooter") was amazing.  Such great recommendations on where to go, what to see, etc.

We went EVERYWHERE.  Literally, we covered the ENTIRE CITY in two days.  We went to breakfast, lunch and dinner... we drove over the Golden Gate Bridge... met friends, took great photos, you name it.  The scooter preformed PERFECTLY.

When we returned it on Monday, I asked "Mr. Scooter" where to go for lunch and he recommended a place that was AMAZING as well.

Its great to rent from someone who knows their product, knows their customers and even knows a great place to eat!!!

Again, I don't write many reviews... but this scooter rental MADE OUR WEEKEND GREAT!< /text>

<user_name>Aubree Dunbar</user_name><Time>1510760309204< /Time><rating>5<//rating>< Text>
Friendly service, very accommodating.  We met the owner, a great hands-on guy who took pride in his business.

We rented a scooter for 10 days to ride around San Francisco and Sausilito.  We even took it to city hall for our marriage ceremony!

There is are many distinct neighborhoods in San Fran, and the scooter was the best way to explore.  The 150cc got us up plenty of hills with no problems.  We rode to the Cliff House, Along the Embarcadero, through Presidio, Little Italy, Chinatown, Haight Street, Golden Gate Park, crossed the Golden Gate Bridge, up to Muir Woods, the Headlands... everywhere.

Parking was easy and traffic was a breeze to get through too. We had a problem with a side mirror after a few days, we brought it in and he fixed it in 15 minutes.  If you want to see San Francisco, rent a scooter from Mr. Scooter.

(I was not given a discount for this review.)< /Text>

<Rating>5</Rating><review>10/3/18:  After having an EV charger installed by Divine, I recalled them for installation of a transfer switch. The live scheduler was courteous and efficient. Nathan Dupre arrived on time to evaluate the job. I could immediately tell that he knows his profession. He spent the time to explain what was needed and required. Unlike other jobs where I understand they present various options and bids, the only options for this job involved the length of an extended warranty. From other reviews I suspect Divine is not the cheapest, but I have learned the hard way that you get what you pay for. Nathan & Bob arrived on time and spent the entire day installing the transfer switch. Both kept the job moving forward and were extremely considerate and polite. The YouTube videos I had seen about installing such a switch did not come close to depicting the actual work involved. In fact Nathan stayed into the early evening to verify the circuits were correct and he will return when the generator can be tested. I never had the sense of any shortcuts. The equipment and the installation will probably outlast me! I rarely write reviews as most services are simply acceptable. Divine stands out and deserves 5 stars.
2/25/19: Most reviews are written soon after one's experience. Today I had a followup visit for the transfer switch which Divine Electric (Nathan) installed last October. I was remiss in not testing it immediately after installation, but a recent 30 hour power outage forced the opportunity to test the generator and transfer switch. All worked well, but I had some operational questions and some thoughts about fine tuning the system. Nathan came out today as planned and spent an hour answering questions and making a few modifications to improve the utility of the set-up. He knew the system because he installed it. "No charge. <Review>Really don't understand the positive reviews. I got the "Seafood Combination" soup ($11.55) and the pork slices appetizer ($11.85).

The soup was basically a large portion of cornstarch and water, a bit of egg white, a couple of shrimp and what'l was possibly an octopus tentacle (or maybe a rubber band, I'm not sure!) It was completely bland, with the most flavor coming from a couple of asparagus stems that tasted fairly fresh. The description said it was supposed to have noodles but there were none in mine.

The pork slices were practically pork jerky, so dry they were hard and felt like bits of plastic. I bought them to feed a dog. He was hungry, so he ate a few but was not interested later, nor was I.< /Review>< Pictures>

< Text>
Gave Lily Kai another chance, and for awhile it was working out. Had a good rapport with the owner, Lily, and everything was good. That was until last night. Called in my order for delivery, spoke to Lily, explained exactly what I wanted and when I got my food, Princess Prawns, the shrimp were like mini rocks. Ever taste food that was over cooked in microwave? Well that's what these shrimp taste like. I called up and complained and of course Lily wasn't there, so the person on the phone had to call her and find out exactly what it was that I wanted. He called me back and asked me if I could pick it up myself. Told him no, I couldn't. Asked him to send me another side dish since mine is now ice cold. He said he was going to charge me for that. After going back and forth, he said my side side dish would be free. 1 hr later I get my Princess Prawns and now they are soggy!
Bottom line........I paid $48 for the meal (this includes another dish for my grandson) and a $20 tip for the guy because I felt bad he had to deliver twice. So $68 for nothing but aggravation, and a bunch of terrible food. I would like my & money back, but I doubt that will happen. I get the "the third time is a charm"), but not this time. I've had enough of Lily Kai! My advice to Lily is........eat the Prawn shrimp and see for yourself how terrible this dish is before you charge the public good $ for that terrible food.< /Text>

<Date>1613762535873</Date><Rating>4< /Rating>< text>
The quintessential LA park.  We go here every day since we live a few blocks away and have dogs.  The weather is usually great even when the rest of the city is getting fog and there's a lot of space for dogs to run around.  We've started to also jog around the park and notice the awesome skyline views of the city and just about every group of stereotypes the city has to offer.  On a warm weekend day it does get a little crowded, but that just adds to the energy you get from coming here.  We also see a lot of picnics, birthday parties, and group gatherings here too.< /text>

<user_id>103664024913169452741<//user_id><Name>Anthony Nava</Name>< Time>
1493793412978</Time>
<rate>5< /rate><Review>Incredible Park that has seen dramatic improvements over the past few years. To name a few: brand new Olympic sized swimming pool that is kept in excellent condition, 2 brand new full sized basketball courts with smooth paving, updated playground for children.

Other amenities include 2 full tennis courts, soccer fields, baseball diamonds, and a skate park. In my opinion no other neighborhood park in LA County comes close.  There is plenty of room for everyone and the grounds are kept up.

My only recommendation would be to install some water fountains that also include a dog fountain at the bottom since so many people walk their dogs there.

There is also the South side of the park that is below the 60 freeway that can be accessed via foot bridge. It includes a large pond that is stocked with fish to enjoy fishing and a small ampitheatre.

To the gentleman who posted a review regarding no shade on the playground, I disagree, the playground and park itself is surrounded with plenty of trees.< /Review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNMMm6pysLwFkqa8ug0aNzJDLdym8jfL8o0d8qZ=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPDzVG2rpc9ELTwYvEaGLW6PZhosn09hvngGeK9=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNSA-rDlYa5jtvRKZl6Z5NbFA-hucAc0-oq_Xlx=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pictures>< Response>

This review is only for the life guards that work at the Belvedere pool. This is my second year coming to enjoy the pool(s) during summer, and almost every time they are seen screaming at children with absent parents. Children that are old enough to go alone, and if they break minor rules they get kicked out of the pool and have to stand on the hot sun for 15 minutes. They are rude and dont have proper training to dicipline children that come to the pool. They should clearly state the rules to everyone before stepping in so they won't end up screaming at everyone because they are breaking rules that are unknown. Just because they are children, does not mean they are not entitled to be respected. They should have the level of professionalism at all times to everyone at the pool.</review>
